import re

def replace_all_non_alphanumeric(text: str) -> str:
    """Replaces all non alphanumeric characters in a string with a space.

    For example:
    ```python
    replace_all_non_alphanumeric("hello world!") == "hello world "
    replace_all_non_alphanumeric("hello_world") == "hello_world"
    replace_all_non_alphanumeric("hello.world") == "hello world"
    ```
    """
    return re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]', ' ', text)
